{"type":"message","id":"3f8eccf8","parentId":"cb07884b","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:01:23.380Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context monitor cron job is firing. Let me read the HEARTBEAT.md if it exists and follow its guidance, then check my memory files for recent context.\n\nLet me first check the heartbeat state and read recent memory files.","thinkingSignature":"4b02fd6fa42f6c1b996c8140ede803ae4a34d6df9ad21c1b0745bc3de788fe95"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vrmsclkch7ui_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\HEARTBEAT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vrmsclkch7ui_2","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"query":"recent tasks projects context state","maxResults":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vrmsclkch7ui_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-19.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":161,"output":161,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":37106,"totalTokens":37428,"cost":{"input":0.00006440000000000001,"output":0.00024150000000000002,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.0055658999999999995,"total":0.0058718}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773932400289}}
{"type":"message","id":"79381c5e","parentId":"3f8eccf8","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:01:23.419Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vrmsclkch7ui_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\n# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Context Manager Check\n\n- Run session_status to check current context usage\n- If context > 60%, consider saving memory and preparing for session switch\n- Check ~/proactivity/session-state.md for active tasks\n- Update ~/proactivity/memory/working-buffer.md if needed\n\n## Self-Improving Check\n\n- Read ./skills/self-improving/heartbeat-rules.md\n- Use ~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md for last-run markers and action notes\n- If no file inside ~/self-improving/ changed since the last reviewed change, return HEARTBEAT_OK\n\n## Proactivity Check\n\n- Read ~/proactivity/heartbeat.md\n- Re-check active blockers, promised follow-ups, stale work, and missing decisions\n- Ask what useful check-in or next move would help right now\n- Message the user only when something changed or needs a decision\n- Update ~/proactivity/session-state.md after meaningful follow-through\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773932483418}}
